Ukraine’s Spring Grain Planting Advanced by 19%, Researcher Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-04-08T11:27:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/ukraine-s-spring-grain-planting-advanced-by-19-researcher-says.html
Ukraine’s spring grain planting
covered 2.07 million hectares (5.1 million acres) as of
yesterday, up 19 percent from a year earlier, according to
researcher UkrAgroConsult.  Barley covered 1.55 million hectares, or half of the
forecast for spring planting, UkrAgroConsult said in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  